The National Chairman of the main opposition party, the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Prince Uche Secondus has felicitated with the Zamfara state Governor Alhaji Bello Matawalle on his victory at the Supreme Court on Friday. Second us also urges the Zamfara State governor to be a good team leader especially as his victory was from God. Prince Secondus urged the Governor and the party in the Zamfara to see this victory as a mandate to work hard to make a lasting mark in the art of governance in the state. ALSO READ: Iju waterworks commences operation The National Chairman who said this in a statement from his media office, signed by his Special Adviser, Ike Abonyi, advised the Governor to unite the people and move quickly to tackle the myriad of challenges facing the state most of which stems from bad governance witnessed in the state in the past. His words: “God has designed this position for you for a purpose and you must do everything humanly possible not to disappoint both the people and the almighty who sent you there. “Identify critical stakeholders who can help you achieve your goals and refuse to be intimidated because you have a special mandate from God.” The national chairman also charged members of the party in the State to cooperate and support the chairman as he executed the mandate they have given him at the poll. NIGERIAN TRIBUNE SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!!